  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*Predicted leading-order asymptotics of the diagonal-twist transfer matrix, generalizing L2's\n  tdiagasympt: the leading (u^3) term is the trivial (κ1+κ2)Id-times-Π(u-θi) coefficient, and the\n  u^2 coefficient is a pure Cartan/total-generator quantity -h[κ(1)E11tot+κ(2)E22tot]. This is the\n  ONLY coefficient below leading that reduces to a c-number formula times a global generator —\n  lower orders genuinely mix different sites' raising/lowering operators and are NOT predicted\n  here (see Task 10's TauEigensystem, where they become the free per-state parameters J1,J0\n  instead of a closed form).*)\nt3diagasympt[λ1_,λ2_,λ3_][u_]:=(κ[1]+κ[2])u^3 IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ1,0}]dim[{λ2,0}]dim[{λ3,0}]] - u^2(κ[1]+κ[2])(θ1+θ2+θ3) IdentityMatrix[dim[{λ1,0}]dim[{λ2,0}]dim[{λ3,0}]] - u^2 h(κ[1] EE[λ1,λ2,λ3][1,1]+κ[2] EE[λ1,λ2,λ3][2,2]);",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*checking asymptotics matches at u^2 order (analog of L2's u^1 check, one order higher since\n  L3's τ(u) is cubic not quadratic). THIS IS THE KEY VALIDATION for the Baxter re-derivation: if\n  this does not collapse to zero, the τ0 formula used from Task 8 onward is wrong and must be\n  re-derived before proceeding — do not patch downstream code around a failure here.*)\nt3diag[1,1,1][1,1][u]-t3diagasympt[1,1,1][u];\nCoefficient[%,u,2]//Simplify",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
