  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*End-to-end Baxter TQ-equation residual check: a(u)Q(u+h) - τ(u)Q(u) + Qθ(u)Q(u-h) = 0, assembled\n  purely from Q1 and τ (which trace back to different derivations — Q1 through\n  QSolve/BaxterMatrix, τ through TauEigensystem's C0/C1/C2 diagonalization — so a small residual\n  here is strong evidence both derivations, including the re-derived L3 M-extraction/J1,J0\n  structure, are correct). Sample points avoid roots of a(u) and Qθ(u). Checked for every (M,n) at\n  (λ1,λ2,λ3)=(1,1,1) and one asymmetric case (2,1,1), mirroring the L2 notebook's regression\n  cases.\n  NOTE: outer sampling loop uses \"uu\" (NOT \"u\") as its Table iteration variable — deliberately\n  distinct from the bare global \"u\" that BaxterMatrix uses internally as its CoefficientList dummy\n  (not Module-localized there). Table's iterator uses dynamic/Block-style binding, so if this loop\n  used \"u\" and triggered a first-time (uncached) QSolve→BaxterMatrix call while \"u\" was numerically\n  bound, BaxterMatrix's internal \"u\" would be clobbered by that bound value instead of acting as a\n  free symbol — exactly the bug the L2 predecessor (Experiments/Baxter_Solver_L2.wb) avoided by\n  using \"uu\" for this same outer loop.*)\ncheckTQ[λ1_, λ2_, λ3_, M_, n_] := Max[Abs[Table[\n    aFun[λ1, λ2, λ3][uu] Q1[λ1, λ2, λ3][M, n][uu + h] - τ[λ1, λ2, λ3][M, n][uu] Q1[λ1, λ2, λ3][M, n][uu] + Qθ[uu] Q1[λ1, λ2, λ3][M, n][uu - h],\n    {uu, {0, 1, 2, -1, 5}}]]];\nTable[{M, n, checkTQ[1, 1, 1, M, n]}, {M, 0, 3}, {n, 0, dPred[M, 1, 1, 1] - 1}] // Flatten[#, 1] &",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
